Power BI Dashboard Design - Reference
=====================================

Pages & Visuals
---------------

[ Page 1: Executive Summary ]
- KPI Card: YTD Revenue
- KPI Card: YTD Units Sold
- KPI Card: AOV (Average Order Value)
- KPI Card: Critical Stock SKUs
- Line chart: Monthly Revenue Trend (last 24 months)
- Bar chart: Revenue by Category
- Forecast line (next 3 months) with confidence band

[ Page 2: Product Performance ]
- Table: Top 20 Selling Products
- Table: Low Selling Products
- Treemap: Revenue by Product
- Slicer: Category
- Slicer: Date range

[ Page 3: Inventory & Stock Coverage ]
- Table: Stock coverage per product
- Conditional formatting: days_of_cover (red < 14, yellow < 30, green > 30)
- Bar chart: Days of cover by product
- Donut chart: Stock status distribution (OK / LOW / CRITICAL / NO_SALES)

[ Page 4: Forecasts ]
- Line chart: Total revenue forecast with upper/lower bounds
- Matrix: Per-product 3-month forecast
- Slicer: Product

Data Sources (PostgreSQL)
-------------------------
- vw_top_selling_products
- vw_low_selling_products
- vw_stock_coverage
- vw_six_month_avg
- vw_monthly_revenue
- forecast_total_revenue
- forecast_product_revenue

Steps in Power BI Desktop
-------------------------
1. Get Data -> PostgreSQL database
2. Provide host, database, and credentials
3. Select the views listed above and load
4. Import the DAX measures from dashboard_measures.dax
5. Build the visuals per the layout above
6. Publish to Power BI Service and schedule a daily refresh
